## Prerequisites

#### PCF Dev uses [VirtualBox](https://www.virtualbox.org) version 5.0 and above as its virtualizer.
1. Download VirtualBox 5.0.14 for OS X hosts [here](http://download.virtualbox.org/virtualbox/5.0.14/VirtualBox-5.0.14-105127-OSX.dmg).
1. Open the .dmg file and double click the VirtualBox.pkg icon.
1. In the pop up that says "This package will run a program to determine if the software can be installed," click Continue.
1. In the installer wizard, click Continue.
1. Select an install destination and click Install.

#### PCF Dev uses [Vagrant](https://www.vagrantup.com/downloads.html) version 1.8.0 and above to run its development environment.
1. Download Vagrant 1.8.1 for Mac OS X hosts [here](https://releases.hashicorp.com/vagrant/1.8.1/vagrant_1.8.1.dmg).
1. Open the .dmg file and double click the Vagrant.pkg icon.
1. In the installer wizard, click Continue.
1. Select an install destination and click Install.

#### PCF Dev uses the [Cloud Foundry command line interface](https://github.com/cloudfoundry/cli) to push and scale apps.
1. To install the cf CLI for Mac OS X 64 bit, download it from [here](https://cli.run.pivotal.io/stable?release=macosx64&source=github). If you previously used the cf CLI v5 Ruby gem, uninstall this gem first.
1. Open the .pkg file.
1. In the installer wizard, click Continue.
1. Select an install destination and click Continue.
1. When prompted, click Install.
1. To verify your installation, open a terminal window and type cf. If your installation was successful, the cf CLI help listing appears.

## Installing PCF Dev
1. Download the latest version of PCF Dev from [Pivotal Network](https://network.pivotal.io/products/pcfdev)
1. Unzip the downloaded zip file.
1. Navigate into the unzipped directory.
1. Run `./start-osx` script in your terminal.

```
unzip pcfdev-VERSION.zip
cd pcfdev-VERSION
./start-osx
```